        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 10:17PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 1017 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 6 miles south of Erwin to 8 miles southwest of
Morganton. Movement was northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Lenoir, Spruce Pine, Newland, Burnsville, Morganton, Gamewell, Glen
Alpine, Banner Elk, Elk Park, and Bakersville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
